### Test Zawaya DAO Contact API
### You can use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code

### Production Endpoints:
### Zawaya Contact: https://contact-api.zawayadao.com/zawaya-contact/submit
### Blockyfy: https://contact-api.zawayadao.com/blockyfy-form/submit

### 1. Health Check (Test if API is running)
GET http://localhost:3005

###

### 2. Submit Zawaya Contact Form with JSON (No file uploads)
POST http://localhost:3005/zawaya-contact/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "message": "I'm interested in Zawaya DAO services. Looking forward to discussing the project.",
  "newsletterSubscribed": true
}

###

### 3. Submit Zawaya Contact Form (Production URL)
POST https://contact-api.zawayadao.com/zawaya-contact/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "message": "Need information about Zawaya DAO blockchain solutions.",
  "newsletterSubscribed": true
}

###

### 4. Submit Form without Message (Optional field)
POST http://localhost:3005/zawaya-contact/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Bob",
  "lastName": "Johnson",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "newsletterSubscribed": true
}

###

### 5. Invalid Request - Missing Required Fields (Should fail)
POST http://localhost:3005/zawaya-contact/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "email": "invalid-test@example.com"
}

###

### 6. Invalid Request - Invalid Email (Should fail)
POST http://localhost:3005/zawaya-contact/submit-json
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "newsletterSubscribed": true
}

